     Most groups like to hang out by the zone so they can run but cry when we get trained and die.  It seems smarter to me to steadily pull single mobs away from the zone.  Everywhere I've been you always get adds anyway.  You always sit and have mana breaks too.  So why is it better to kill 3...wait....kill 3...wait... rather than steadily kill singles without mana breaks or the risk of multi mobs.<br>
     Any advice out there for a noob trying to learn how to pull? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iskandaralazeem>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1152<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/03 6:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice about pulling</span><hr size=1> People are impatient. =) Or stupid for not realizing the capabilities of the group.<br>
<br>
If you've got some reliable crowd control (root/mezz/whatever) then multiples aren't much of a concern. Get used to multiples as you'll see them more often as you level and outgrow outdoor zones. With that being said, never, ever, ever let people bully you into pulling faster. If everyone's mana never dips below 60-80,<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> that's</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a sign that faster pulls might be good.<br>
<br>
The next time a caster bitches about slow pulls, you can always do what I did and ask him if he'd like to pull. Usually they just get really quiet. =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/03 11:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice about pulling</span><hr size=1> It's really hard for warriors to chain pull unless you're not tanking, and at lower levels it is fairly rare for a warrior not to be tanking unless there are characters with significant equipment advantage.<br>
<br>
If your group seems to have more than enough mana to handle the mobs, you can always have multiple pullers. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aakla2>aakla2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 3:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://pages.prodigy.net/mikekling/Smilies/babytumbleI.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice about pulling</span><hr size=1> It all depends on your group really.<br>
